   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Terms of Use Settings</uicontrol> section enables you to set the terms of use for the general public while using the Public Portal. This Terms of Use is displayed in the Public Portal for the general public's awareness.</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol> page, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol>, and then select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Application Settings</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Application Settings</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Terms of Use Settings</uicontrol> section, enter the terms of use that you want to define for the general public while using public portal.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note "> The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Terms of Use</uicontrol> defined here is displayed in the public portal. It is mandatory for the general public to read the terms of use before submitting their feedback.</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
